				<div itemprop="commentText" class='post entry-content '>
					<!--cached-Mon, 21 Jul 2014 05:00:17 +0000-->I managed to remove the X-PHP reference from the mail module in my admin folder by replacing<br /><br /><pre class='prettyprint lang-auto linenums:0'>
while (&#036;mail = tep_db_fetch_array(&#036;mail_query)) {
      &#036;mimemessage-&gt;send(&#036;mail&#91;&#39;customers_firstname&#39;&#93; . &#39; &#39; . &#036;mail&#91;&#39;customers_lastname&#39;&#93;, &#036;mail&#91;&#39;customers_email_address&#39;&#93;, &#39;&#39;, &#036;from, &#036;subject);
    }
</pre><br />with <br /><br /><pre class='prettyprint lang-auto linenums:0'>
// before sending mail, change PHP_SELF to hide admin dir from mail header
    &#036;tempvar = &#036;HTTP_SERVER_VARS&#91;&#39;PHP_SELF&#39;&#93;;
    &#036;HTTP_SERVER_VARS&#91;&#39;PHP_SELF&#39;&#93; = &quot;/mail.php&quot;;
    while (&#036;mail = tep_db_fetch_array(&#036;mail_query)) {
      &#036;mimemessage-&gt;send(&#036;mail&#91;&#39;customers_firstname&#39;&#93; . &#39; &#39; . &#036;mail&#91;&#39;customers_lastname&#39;&#93;, &#036;mail&#91;&#39;customers_email_address&#39;&#93;, &#39;&#39;, &#036;from, &#036;subject);
    }
    &#036;HTTP_SERVER_VARS&#91;&#39;PHP_SELF&#39;&#93; = &#036;tempvar;
</pre><br />however, I don&#39;t find this code in the Orders.php file. The only code I find is a tep_mail action but I don&#39;t have an idea on how to change/alter this to hide the x-php referencen my php knowledge doesn&#39;t reach that far. any help is appreciated, the linked topic above doesn&#39;t really specify this.
					
